    "what_description": "Tepualia stipularis is a species of flowering plant in the family Myrtaceae, native to South America. It is an evergreen shrub or small tree that grows up to 10 meters in height, with a trunk diameter of up to 30 centimeters. The leaves are lanceolate, alternate, and simple, measuring 5-10 centimeters in length and 1-2 centimeters in width, with a petiole 2-5 millimeters long and a stipule 1-2 millimeters long. The inflorescence is a corymb, bearing white or pale yellow flowers with 5 petals, 8-10 stamens, and 5 styles. The fruit is a berry, 10-15 millimeters in diameter, with 5-6 seeds.",
